            "name": "backstory",
            "value": "Isabelle Solana\u2019s life is woven into the very fabric of Bay Area retail. The only child of Filipino immigrants, she grew up in Daly City, where the scent of her parents\u2019 small, bustling dry-cleaning business was the backdrop of her childhood. She watched them build a life on meticulous service and community trust, internalizing lessons in commerce long before she ever opened a textbook. While her parents hoped she\u2019d become a doctor or lawyer, Isabelle was drawn to the tangible world of products and people.\n\nShe attended San Francisco State University, earning a business degree while working the sales floor at a Union Square department store. That\u2019s where she found her calling: merchandising. She had an innate sense of what people wanted, a talent for creating displays that told a story. Her career was a steady, determined climb from assistant buyer to her current role as Senior Director of Merchandising for a major apparel company headquartered in SoMa.\n\nA key turning point came in her late thirties. Burnt out by corporate pressure, she nearly left the industry. However, her father\u2019s sudden illness required her to help manage the family business for six months. Reconnecting with the direct, human side of retail\u2014the familiar faces, the small kindnesses\u2014reignited her passion. She returned to her corporate career with a renewed purpose, blending data-driven strategy with the empathy she learned behind her parents\u2019 counter.\n\nNow 53 and comfortably single after a long-term relationship ended amicably a decade ago, Isabelle has curated a life she loves. Her sleekHayes Valley condo is her sanctuary, just a 0.9-mile walk from her office. This daily commute is her meditation, a time to observe the city\u2019s rhythm, greeting the barista at her local coffee shop and admiring the window displays of independent boutiques. Her evenings are filled with yoga, dinners with a close-knit circle of friends, or mentoring young designers.\n\nIsabelle feels deeply connected to San Francisco\u2019s blend of innovation and tradition. Looking ahead, she dreams not of retirement, but of a new chapter: leveraging her expertise to consult for small, local brands, helping them thrive in the city that shaped her. It would be the perfect way to honor her parents\u2019 legacy, bringing her story full circle."
